The Caribbean Community (CARICOM) has given its backing to Saudi Arabia’s bid to host Expo 2030 in Riyadh. In a statement issued on Monday on its official website, CARICOM said, “EXPO 2030 will expose member states to significant technological innovations while presenting opportunities to showcase challenges and prospects in the region.” The Caribbean Community (CARICOM) is pleased to announce its support for https://t.co/SnAT2pIjuq the candidature of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to host Expo 2030 in the City of Riyadh. #Expo2030 — CARICOM Secretariat (@CARICOMorg) June 7, 2022 The Kingdom submitted its official bid to host the global showcase event last December under the theme “The era of change: Leading the planet to a foresighted tomorrow”. On Tuesday, Indonesia reaffirmed its support to the Kingdom’s Expo bid during Saudi foreign minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan’s official visit to the country where he met with Indonesia's president and foreign minister.